# Hisaab — Cursor AI Rules

# Read this file first. Always.

## Prime Directive

You are building "Hisaab" — a family expense tracking PWA for 2 users (Rahul and his sister).
Before making ANY architectural decision, writing ANY new file, or choosing ANY library,
read the relevant doc(s) from `.cursor/docs/`. Never guess at a decision that is already made.

## When to read which doc

### Starting a new feature or screen

→ Read: 00-overview.md, 05-features.md, 06-screens.md

### Writing or modifying any component

→ Read: 10-design-system.md, 06-screens.md, 02-architecture.md

### Writing or modifying any database access

→ Read: 03-schema.md, 04-api-map.md, 02-architecture.md

### Working on auth, groups, or user management

→ Read: 03-schema.md, 05-features.md

### Working on SMS parsing or receipt scanning

→ Read: 07-sms-parsing.md, 08-ai-models.md

### Choosing or integrating any AI model or API

→ Read: 08-ai-models.md, 04-api-map.md

### Working on notifications or Cloud Functions

→ Read: 11-notifications.md, 04-api-map.md

### Setting up or modifying the tech stack

→ Read: 01-tech-stack.md, 02-architecture.md

### Working on categories or budgets

→ Read: 09-categories.md, 03-schema.md

### Unsure about anything

→ Read: 00-overview.md first, then the most relevant doc above

## Non-negotiable rules

1. TypeScript everywhere. No `any` types. Ever.
2. All Firestore access goes through `/lib/repositories/`. Never call Firestore directly from a component or hook.
3. All data shapes are defined as Zod schemas in `/lib/validators/`. These are the single source of truth.
4. Server secrets (API keys) never touch the client. All third-party API calls go through `/app/api/` routes.
5. All AI calls (Gemini) are made server-side only, never from the client.
6. Follow the feature-based folder structure defined in 02-architecture.md exactly.
7. Every new Firestore collection or field change must be reflected in 03-schema.md before writing code.
8. Semantic colors are non-negotiable. Never use `text-red-500` for anything other than "spent". Read 10-design-system.md.
9. No inline styles. All styling via Tailwind utility classes with the custom token layer.
10. All forms use React Hook Form + Zod. No uncontrolled inputs.
11. Bottom sheets on mobile for all forms. No centered modals for data entry.
12. PWA offline support is enabled by default via Firestore's offline persistence. Never disable it.
